Website - Bhuvan Planner
Website URL - https://bhuvan-app2.nrsc.gov.in/planner/
Website Content Details -
Bhuvan Planner is a geospatial planning portal developed by the National Remote Sensing Centre (NRSC) of the Indian Space Research Organisation (ISRO). It is a web-based platform that provides a variety of tools and resources for planning and development at the gram panchayat level.

Bhuvan Planner includes a variety of spatial datasets, including:

Land use and land cover
Natural resources
Infrastructure
Socio-economic data
These datasets can be used to create maps, analyze data, and generate reports. Bhuvan Planner also includes a variety of tools for planning and development, such as:

Land use planning
Infrastructure planning
Natural resource management
Disaster management
Bhuvan Planner is a valuable tool for gram panchayats and other local governments in India. It can be used to improve planning and decision-making, and to promote sustainable development.

Here are some specific examples of how Bhuvan Planner can be used:

A gram panchayat can use Bhuvan Planner to create a land use plan that identifies the best uses for land in the panchayat. This plan can help to ensure that land is used efficiently and sustainably.
A gram panchayat can use Bhuvan Planner to assess the needs for infrastructure, such as roads, schools, and hospitals. This information can be used to prioritize investments and improve the quality of life for residents.
A gram panchayat can use Bhuvan Planner to monitor natural resources, such as water and forests. This information can be used to manage resources sustainably and to prevent disasters.
Bhuvan Planner is a powerful tool that can be used to improve planning and development at the local level in India. It is a valuable resource for gram panchayats, other local governments, and other stakeholders.
